_header: Of humility and lowliness cometh grace
_description: Pride and Envy destroy Virtue — one couplet

TCD69.Transcription:
Of humylitie and lowlines comethe graceBut whear as pride and enuye
                    is vertue hath no place
TCD69.Note:
Added in a 16th century hand, with a second hand writing a second,
                    garbled version.
